parameters: Umi: "Thank you very much!"
Customer: "I'll come again!"
Umi: "Phew..."

Shop Owner: "Well... Umi-chan! Good work! You've done a great job today as
well!"
Umi: "No... not at all! I can still keep working!"

Shop Owner: "Hahaha! Well, the busyness is all thanks to Umi-chan and your
recipes! You've got to take responsibility!"
Umi: "Hahaha! I'll do my best!"

Shop Owner: "Hahaha! Just kidding! Thanks as always... but I'm worried
about you working so much... You even turned down that marriage proposal
from the nobleman, didn't you?"
Umi: "...Yes"
Shop Owner: "No matter how much you think about your late husband..."
Umi: "Mia! You're hurt again!"

Shop Owner: "Is it those brats' doing again? Next time I see them, I'll
give them a piece of my mind! Are you okay, Mia-chan?"
Mia: "It hurt, but... a kind big brother helped me!"
Umi: "Big brother?"

Mia: "Yeah! He said he'd kill them if he caught them bullying again, and he
chased them away!"
Umi: "Kill?"
Shop Owner: "...Ah... that's kind of scary in its own way."
Shopkeeper: "Umi-chan will be back soon, you know."
Mia: "Yeah... Thank you for the meal, auntie! It was delicious!"
Shopkeeper: "Is that so? I'm glad to hear it!"
Mia: "Auntie... why doesn't mom get remarried, I wonder..."
Shopkeeper: "Mia-chan..."

Mia: "You said that dad died right after I was born... but sometimes I see
mom looking very lonely."
Shopkeeper: "Is that so..."
Mia: "I feel very lonely too, wishing dad was here..."

Shopkeeper: "...That's right... Mia-chan, forgetting someone you love is a
very difficult thing to do."
Mia: "Is that true?"
Shopkeeper: "It is..."
Mia: "I see. So mom must have really loved dad, huh?"
Shopkeeper: "That's right."
Mia: "Auntie, this..."
Shopkeeper: "What's this book?"

Mia: "This is a diary? A book? that mom writes in sometimes... I brought it
here without asking."
Shopkeeper: "Oh my! That's... that's not good..."

Mia: "But... I thought maybe it has something written about dad... But I
can't read yet..."
Shopkeeper: "I see... Mia-chan wants to know about her father too, huh."
Mia: "So please! Read it to me, just a little!"
Shopkeeper: "Eh! But that's..."
Mia: "Please!"
Shopkeeper: "...Well... just a little bit then..."
Mia: "Thank you!"
*Flipping pages*
Shopkeeper: "Eh... what's this... hey, Kru... do you remember?"
Mia: "Kru? Could that be dad's name⁉"
Shopkeeper: "It might be... let's see here."
Umi: "I'm back!"
*Startled*
Mia: "Oh no oh no oh no oh no... what should we do!"
Shopkeeper: "For now, let's hide it under the table!"
Umi: "I've finished the errands."
Shopkeeper: "Oh... yeah! Thank you so much!"
Mia: "Mom!... Welcome back!"
Umi: "Hmm... suspicious..."
*Nervous*
Mia: "Oh no oh no oh no oh no..."
Shopkeeper: "There's there's there's nothing like that"

Umi: "...Don't tell me... Mia! You left vegetables on your plate again,
didn't you⁉"
Mia: "Huh? Ah..."
Shopkeeper: "Ah... that's right! Mia-chan left some behind..."
Mia: "Mia ate properly!"
Umi: "Can't be helped... Make sure to eat properly next time, okay?"
Shopkeeper: "Next time... I'll make sure she eats properly."
Mia: "Hmph... even though I ate properly..."
